          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5271 lnet: debug patch for o2iblnd",
        "message": "LU-5271 lnet: debug patch for o2iblnd\n\nIf ib_poll_cq returned +ve even without initialising ib_wc,\nthen o2iblnd will run into unpredictable situation because\no2iblnd unconditionally trust ib_wc::wr_id as user defined data\nwhich should always be pointer of tx/rx.\n\nThis patch can verify this conjecture. If this is true, the LASSERTF\nshould be changed to CWARN.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2b287af97db98d97f562a3ba8d1d8046d02d482c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
